00:00:22.970 --> 00:00:24.250
I'm going to look through.

00:00:24.250 --> 00:00:27.320
What I'm going to do is pick one
of the cards and memorize

00:00:27.320 --> 00:00:28.660
where it is in the deck.

00:00:28.660 --> 00:00:31.540
So I'm going to pick one of
these cards, and then what I'm

00:00:31.540 --> 00:00:35.670
going to do is count how many
cards are on top of it.

00:00:35.670 --> 00:00:39.090
And I'm going to remember both
the card I'm thinking of, and

00:00:39.090 --> 00:00:41.190
the number of cards above it.

00:00:41.190 --> 00:00:42.020
OK, got it, got it.

00:00:42.020 --> 00:00:42.940
OK, so I'll remember.

00:00:42.940 --> 00:00:44.930
I'm remembering one card in this
deck, and I'm remembering

00:00:44.930 --> 00:00:45.560
where it is.

00:00:45.560 --> 00:00:49.360
What I'm going to do now is
I'm going to broadcast the

00:00:49.360 --> 00:00:51.530
number of card into
Brady's mind.

00:00:51.530 --> 00:00:51.840
All right?

00:00:51.840 --> 00:00:53.200
So I'm thinking of a
number of cards.

00:00:53.200 --> 00:00:55.530
I'm going to send that
number into his mind.

00:00:55.530 --> 00:00:58.640
He's going to tell me that
number that I've sent to him,

00:00:58.640 --> 00:01:00.200
and then we're going to
count off that many.

00:01:00.200 --> 00:01:03.490
And the next one will be the
card I'm remembering.

00:01:03.490 --> 00:01:05.860
Skeptical people may say you're
